definitions.definition: (of a vehicle or its engine) provided with a turbocharger.
(of wind) move creating an air current.
examples: a cold wind began to blow
synonyms: storm "the icy wind blew around us"

definitions.definition: (of wind) cause to move; propel.
examples: a gust of wind blew a cloud of smoke into his face
synonyms: force "his ship was blown on to the rocks"

definitions.definition: be carried, driven, or moved by the wind or an air current.
examples: it was so windy that the tent nearly blew away

definitions.definition: leave (a place).
examples: I'm ready to blow town

definitions.definition: (of a person) expel air through pursed lips.
examples: Willie took a deep breath, and blew

definitions.definition: use one's breath to propel.
examples: he blew cigar smoke in her face

definitions.definition: breathe hard; pant.
examples: Uncle Albert was soon puffing and blowing

definitions.definition: cause to breathe hard; exhaust of breath.
examples: adjective: blown

definitions.definition: (of a person) force air through the mouth into (an instrument) in order to make a sound.
examples: the umpire blew his whistle

definitions.definition: (of such an instrument) make a noise by having air forced through it.
examples: police whistles blew

definitions.definition: sound (the horn of a vehicle).
play jazz or rock music in an unrestrained style.
examples: it took him maybe five choruses to warm up, but then he could really blow

definitions.definition: force air through a tube into (molten glass) in order to create an artifact.
remove the contents of (an egg) by forcing air through it.
(of flies) lay eggs in or on something.
examples: to repel the hordes of flies that would otherwise blow on the buffalo hide

definitions.definition: (of a whale) eject air and vapor through the blowhole.
(of an explosion or explosive device) displace violently or send flying.
examples: the blast had blown the windows out of the van

definitions.definition: (of a vehicle tire) burst suddenly while the vehicle is in motion.
burst or cause to burst due to pressure or overheating.
examples: the engines sounded as if their exhausts had blown

definitions.definition: (of an electrical circuit) burn out or cause to burn out through overloading.
examples: the fuse in the plug had blown

definitions.definition: spend recklessly.
examples: they blew $100,000 in just eighteen months
synonyms: use up; Morespend recklessly; informalsplurge "he blew his money on gambling"

definitions.definition: completely lose or miss (an opportunity).
examples: the wider issues were to show that politicians had blown it

definitions.definition: expose (a stratagem).
examples: a man whose cover was blown

definitions.definition: damn.
examples: “Well, blow me ,” he said, “I never knew that”

definitions.definition: perform fellatio.
produce flowers or be in flower.
examples: I know a bank where the wild thyme blows
